      <hedline>
        <hl1>PRIZE WINNER</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By George James</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">James, Greg</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>NASA scientist James E Hansen, credited with alerting public to global warming, is named winner of $250,000 Heinz Award for people who enhance lives of others (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>James E. Hansen, a NASA scientist credited with alerting the public to global warming, has been named a winner of of the Heinz Award, which honors people who enhance the lives of others. Mr. Hansen, 59, lives in Ridgewood  and is director of the NASA's Goddard Institute of Space Studies in Manhattan. He gave the first warnings about how industrial pollution is changing the climate in testimony before a Congressional panel in 1988. The $250,000 award will be presented in Washington March 5.</p>
        <p>George James</p>
      </block>
